title:Boiled Maple Frosting
ingredients:2 cups sugar//
1/2 cup water//
2/3 cup maple syrup//
1 Tablespoon light corn syrup//
2 egg whites//
1/4 tablespoon cream of tatar//
1 teaspoon vanilla//
Dash of salt
instructions:Put sugar, water, maple syrup, and corn syrup in a saucepan.//
Stir over low heat until the sugar dissolves.//
Boil, covered, about 3 minutes.//
Boil uncovered without siring until a small amount of syrup forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.//
Remove from heat.//
Beat the egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry.//
Pour syrup in fine stream over egg whites, beating constantly.//
Add salt and vanilla, and continue beating until cool and able to spread.//
